23/05/2010
ANKARA, Turkey -- Kemal Kilicdaroglu was elected as president of the main opposition Republican People's Party (CHP) at Ð° congress on Saturday (May 22nd). He replaces long-time leader Deniz Baykal, who resigned on May 10th. Kemal Kilicdaroglu, 61, said his priority will be to fight poverty, unemployment and corruption. His nomination was backed by 1,189 out of 1,197 delegates. (Hurriyet, Anadolu news agency, AFP, Reuters, AP, DPA - 22/05/10) 
